            <div>
                <h2 class="heade center">Front End</h2>
                <p class="center">The front end refers to the part of a website that users interact with directly.It
                    includes everything a user sees on the web page such as button,text,images,forms,and overall
                    layout.The goal of front-end development is to make the user experience(UX) smooth,efficint,and
                    visually appealing.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2 class="heade center">Back End</h2>
                <p class="center">The back end is the behind-the-scenes functionality that powers the website. It
                    handles the server-side operations,databases,and application logic that the usre doesn't see.It
                    ensure that the information entered on the front end is processed and stored properly.The back end
                    is responsible for responding to requests,processing data,and managing connections to databases and
                    servers.</p>
            </div>
            </P>
        </div>
